sentence: Hein was a close associate of Martin Gardner and his work was frequently featured in Gardner's Mathematical Games column in Scientific American. The game of Hex (July 1957), the Soma cube (Sep 1958), the game of Tangloids (Dec 1959) and The Superellipse (Sep 1965) At the age of 95 Gardner wrote his autobiography and titled it Undiluted Hocus-Pocus.
